# Security Standards

## Core Principles

### 1. Zero Trust
- Never trust user input — validate everything
- Assume breach — defense in depth
- Verify explicitly — authenticate every request
- Least privilege — minimal permissions

### 2. Defense in Depth
- Multiple layers of controls
- Fail securely — default deny on errors
- Log security events
- Encrypt in transit (TLS) and at rest

### 3. Security by Design
- Threat modeling during planning
- Security in definition of done
- Secure defaults — opt-in for risky features

